    "summary": "Ronald Boellaard has a background in biology (MSc) and physics (MSc) and a PhD in science. His research focuses on (pharmacokinetic) quantitative analysis of positron emission tomography (PET), PET image reconstruction and processing. He obtained several grants, such as the VIDI grant of the Netherlands Organisation for Scientific Research. He is member of several international societies and committees (QIBA technical FDG PET/CT committee, member of EANM physics committee, EORTC imaging workgroup, etc). He has authored and coauthored more than 400 peer reviewed papers and has a H-index >65 (83 google scolar). He is the principal author for the Netherlands and the European guideline for standardisation of quantitative FDG PET and PET/CT studies (EJNMMI 2010 & 2015). In 2023 he received the Edward J Hoffman award from the SNMMI Physics, Instrumentation and Data Science council.\n\n\nSpecialties: \n- Quantitative analysis of positron emission tomography studies\n- Image processing\n- Image reconstruction\n- Pharmacokinetic analysis (brain, onco, cardio)\n- Central data analysis and QA\n- Standardisation and harmonisation (founder of EARL PET accreditation program)\n- Radiomics and machine learning\n- Artificial intelligence",
